onably approximated by (1/$a_{\\rm 1}$)(d$a_{\\rm\n1}$/d$t$)=$\\left(2.22{\\times}10^{-8}{\\rm\nyrs}^{-1}\\right)4q\\left(1+q\\right)^{-2}(R_{\\rm 3}/100{\\rm\nR}_{\\odot})^{5.2}(a_{\\rm 1}/0.2{\\rm AU})^{4.8}(a_{\\rm 2}/2{\\rm AU})^{-10.2}$\n$({\\tau}/0.534{\\rm yrs})^{-1.0}$. We also provide tests of how precise this\nfitting function is.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 28 Oct 2019 17:58:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-08"}
